    <abstract id="aspace_3410e76095dece862fecb15d8e33f3ed">These invoices, dated 1849, pertain to the opening and grading of streets in the Gowanus area of Brooklyn between Gowanus Ditch and Hamilton Avenue. Gowanus Ditch was a small channel connecting the Atlantic Basin to the Gowanus Canal. The invoices were submitted to the City of Brooklyn by James Ashfield, the contractor who completed the work.</abstract>
